10:21.370 --> 10:24.072
Hey.

10:24.107 --> 10:25.941
Where's my daughter?

10:26.958 --> 10:28.601
_

10:30.813 --> 10:31.813
Hey!

10:35.051 --> 10:36.051
Ugh!

10:59.075 --> 11:02.010
[wincing]

11:02.044 --> 11:04.212
Irisa!

11:04.247 --> 11:05.514
[groaning]

11:14.757 --> 11:17.592
Kiddo, hey, hey.

11:17.627 --> 11:20.262
Hey, kiddo.

11:20.296 --> 11:23.999
Hey, you okay?

11:24.033 --> 11:25.000
You okay?

11:25.034 --> 11:26.067
Your breath stinks.

11:26.102 --> 11:27.702
Oh, you're all right.

11:27.737 --> 11:31.506
All right.
Oh, oh.

11:31.541 --> 11:33.041
Come on.

11:33.075 --> 11:36.077
[both grunting]

11:41.184 --> 11:43.385
How'd we get here?

11:43.419 --> 11:45.787
Where are we?

11:48.925 --> 11:50.091
Thank Christ.

11:50.126 --> 11:53.094
[dramatic music]

11:53.129 --> 11:56.136
♪ ♪

11:56.221 --> 12:01.221
Sync and corrections by explosiveskull
www.addic7ed.com

12:05.779 --> 12:09.432
_

12:14.283 --> 12:15.417
Any movement?

12:15.451 --> 12:19.221
No. No patrols.

12:19.255 --> 12:22.290
Good.

12:22.325 --> 12:25.126
Come quickly then.

12:25.161 --> 12:26.161
We spotted them.

12:34.337 --> 12:36.638
Bundle up, dear.

12:36.672 --> 12:38.740
It's a walk.

12:58.961 --> 13:02.430
It's an old joint Pilar's
parents had when she was little.

13:02.465 --> 13:03.665
Only my wife
would be crazy enough

13:03.699 --> 13:05.700
to hole up
behind enemy lines.

13:08.271 --> 13:10.272
Our grandchild.

13:12.108 --> 13:14.876
Have you seen
Alak and Christie?

13:14.911 --> 13:17.545
Not yet.
They're probably inside.

13:19.115 --> 13:21.349
If your wife has harmed them,

13:21.384 --> 13:26.021
she will die
an excruciating death.

13:26.055 --> 13:29.491
And if
she hasn't harmed them?

13:29.525 --> 13:31.760
Same outcome.

13:31.794 --> 13:33.662
I see your point.

13:33.696 --> 13:35.363
How do we get down there?

13:35.398 --> 13:37.365
Well, the incline's too steep.

13:37.400 --> 13:39.868
We've got to go
around the long way.

13:39.902 --> 13:42.003
Come on.
Let's get back to the roller.

13:58.187 --> 13:59.554
[sighs]

13:59.588 --> 14:03.124
Nothing like the cold air
to ward off croup.

14:03.159 --> 14:04.459
Does he need to be changed?

14:04.493 --> 14:06.227
Yeah, but don't worry,
honey.

14:06.262 --> 14:08.463
Grandma's got little Lukey.

14:33.823 --> 14:37.025
[tense music]

14:37.059 --> 14:38.593
Votanis Collective
death squad.

14:38.627 --> 14:41.229
They've taken our vehicle.

14:41.263 --> 14:43.131
Ah, <i>chup.</i>

14:43.165 --> 14:45.066
♪ ♪

14:45.101 --> 14:48.470
We can't let them
discover the children.

14:48.504 --> 14:53.375
All right.
Make it look good.

14:53.409 --> 15:01.116
♪ ♪

15:01.150 --> 15:03.685
- Move.
- Take it easy!

15:06.877 --> 15:07.657
_

15:08.093 --> 15:09.867
_

15:10.179 --> 15:11.382
_

15:12.016 --> 15:15.054
_

15:15.289 --> 15:17.098
_

15:17.722 --> 15:19.758
_

15:19.835 --> 15:21.970
Loyal to the Collective?

15:22.004 --> 15:25.240
I shall be the judge of that.

15:25.274 --> 15:27.776
I am General Rahm Tak.

15:27.810 --> 15:29.044
The Beast.

15:29.078 --> 15:31.179
You've heard of me?

15:31.213 --> 15:33.848
I, however,
find myself at a disadvantage.

15:33.883 --> 15:37.652
I am Datak Tarr
of the <i>Shanje Liro.</i>

15:37.686 --> 15:40.822
Ah. I know the name.

15:40.856 --> 15:42.323
You're from Defiance.

15:42.358 --> 15:44.426
A self-styled crime lord,
are you not?

15:44.460 --> 15:46.194
I've learned
to make some small profit

15:46.228 --> 15:47.395
among the humans.

15:47.430 --> 15:49.364
Small indeed.

15:49.398 --> 15:54.436
Your donations to our common
cause have been meager, at best,

15:54.470 --> 15:57.005
and you're only <i>Shanje</i>
by marriage.

15:58.875 --> 16:00.355
_

16:01.106 --> 16:06.518
_

16:07.006 --> 16:10.408
_

16:11.087 --> 16:12.587
Who's the pink skin?

16:12.621 --> 16:14.989
Who you calling pink skin,
you Edgar Winter piece of <i>sht...</i>

16:15.017 --> 16:16.130
_

16:16.685 --> 16:18.446
_

16:19.995 --> 16:21.329
McCawley.

16:21.363 --> 16:23.698
The name is Rafe McCawley.

16:23.732 --> 16:27.469
Please don't kill him.
The human is our bounty.

16:27.503 --> 16:30.338
There is a price on his head
back in Defiance.

16:30.372 --> 16:31.573
[laughs]

16:31.607 --> 16:33.675
You are in luck.

16:33.709 --> 16:36.578
My caravan is headed
to your hometown.

16:36.612 --> 16:38.880
We'll make camp here.

16:38.914 --> 16:41.950
We can travel together,
once we've eaten and rested.

16:41.984 --> 16:44.352
I won't take "no"
for an answer.

16:44.386 --> 16:47.489
I've been dying
for some cultured company.

16:47.523 --> 16:48.723
General Tak,

16:48.757 --> 16:51.526
may I ask what business
you have in Defiance?

16:51.560 --> 16:53.027
You may, indeed.

16:53.062 --> 16:55.997
I'm going to kill all the humans
and burn the disgusting place

16:56.031 --> 16:57.132
to the ground.

17:04.395 --> 17:05.633
Your winnings.

17:08.141 --> 17:09.642
Okay, you don't have to do that.

17:09.675 --> 17:11.444
- It's all there.
- I count by twos.

17:11.478 --> 17:13.746
It goes fast.

17:13.780 --> 17:16.582
She's gonna need it to pay
her way across the Badlands.

17:16.616 --> 17:17.983
What are you talking about?

17:23.056 --> 17:24.656
What's with the packed bags?

17:24.691 --> 17:26.425
Excuse me.

17:26.460 --> 17:28.294
I've got a ticket
on tomorrow's land coach.

17:28.328 --> 17:30.296
Thought I'd try my luck
out west.

17:30.330 --> 17:31.831
This town needs you.

17:31.865 --> 17:34.867
What this town needs is
a sensitively worded obituary.

17:34.901 --> 17:37.803
Defiance has faced
harder winters than this.

17:37.838 --> 17:40.840
[sighs]
It's time to get real.

17:40.874 --> 17:44.110
It's been seven months since
the McCawley mines collapsed.

17:44.144 --> 17:45.845
Gulanite was the lifeblood
of this town.

17:45.879 --> 17:48.080
There is no future
without it.

17:48.115 --> 17:49.582
Oh, and incidentally,

17:49.616 --> 17:52.351
I just heard
that the stasis nets went down.

17:52.386 --> 17:53.486
Amanda, is that true?

17:53.520 --> 17:54.553
It's temporary.

17:54.588 --> 17:56.422
Ah, so we're only
temporarily screwed.

17:56.456 --> 17:57.990
- Good news.
- Ow.

17:58.025 --> 18:00.159
I depart
with a clear conscience.

18:00.193 --> 18:03.496
Look, we've lost
soldiers, doctors, engineers,

18:03.530 --> 18:06.165
anyone with a skill
marketable to the outside world,

18:06.199 --> 18:07.666
but you know who stayed?

18:07.701 --> 18:08.901
The people who can't leave.

18:08.935 --> 18:10.636
The people who can't survive
in the Badlands.

18:10.670 --> 18:12.271
Yeah, and they're depending
on people like us

18:12.305 --> 18:14.140
to keep it all together.

18:14.174 --> 18:15.141
Come on, Doc.

18:15.175 --> 18:17.977
You're the only doctor in town.

18:18.011 --> 18:20.312
If you leave, people will die.

18:20.347 --> 18:21.614
I don't want that
on my conscience,

18:21.648 --> 18:23.816
and I don't think
you do either.

18:23.850 --> 18:26.619
The fact that you try
to appeal to my better angels

18:26.653 --> 18:30.556
is adorably human.

18:30.590 --> 18:33.192
So you're staying?

18:33.226 --> 18:35.261
Get your skinny ass
out of here.

18:35.295 --> 18:36.929
I've got work to do.

18:40.100 --> 18:44.370
(Nolan)
Last thing I remember, uh,

18:44.404 --> 18:46.872
- _
- was the ceiling coming down on us.

18:46.907 --> 18:49.642
You were in my arms, and...

18:49.676 --> 18:52.945
I pulled you
into one of those life pods,

18:52.979 --> 18:55.047
and it closed up around.

18:55.082 --> 18:56.749
We must have gone to sleep.

18:56.783 --> 19:00.152
I wake up, and we're being
pulled out by something.

19:00.187 --> 19:02.455
Some alien
I've never seen before.

19:02.489 --> 19:03.956
Older male.
Younger female.

19:03.990 --> 19:05.224
Purple skin.
Real strong.

19:05.258 --> 19:08.360
This ringing a bell for you?

19:08.395 --> 19:09.728
They cut you?

19:13.433 --> 19:15.401
Yeah, must have.
You got one too.

19:21.875 --> 19:23.342
[sighs]

19:26.580 --> 19:28.814
Defiance is that way.

19:28.849 --> 19:30.683
We should probably go soon.

19:30.717 --> 19:32.351
I can't go back.

19:32.385 --> 19:34.019
They're gonna lynch me.

19:34.054 --> 19:37.656
It's the only town.

19:37.691 --> 19:39.825
They know I'm a mass murderer.

19:39.860 --> 19:42.228
I destroyed New York.

19:42.262 --> 19:45.364
Nolan, I killed Tommy.

19:47.167 --> 19:48.767
All right.

19:48.802 --> 19:51.303
Now, you listen up because
I'm only gonna say this once.

19:51.338 --> 19:53.005
It was that arkbrain
that did the killing,

19:53.039 --> 19:54.640
not you.

19:54.674 --> 19:57.376
You are as much a victim
as anyone.

19:57.410 --> 19:58.777
You fought it.

19:58.812 --> 20:02.815
You beat it,
and you saved everyone.

20:04.317 --> 20:06.218
I could not be prouder of you.

20:08.155 --> 20:09.688
They're still gonna lynch me.

20:09.723 --> 20:11.190
Details, details.

20:15.228 --> 20:17.496
(Irisa)
What is that?

20:17.531 --> 20:19.098
It's a wormhole flare.

20:19.132 --> 20:20.566
Long-distance coded message.

20:20.600 --> 20:22.101
Votanis Collective.

20:22.135 --> 20:24.403
The V.C. isn't normally
this far north.

20:24.437 --> 20:26.272
I wonder
who they're talking to.

20:26.306 --> 20:29.308
[shouting in native language]

20:36.316 --> 20:39.585
What's the message?

20:39.619 --> 20:41.587
It's good.

20:41.621 --> 20:44.557
Just got word from Defiance,
the stasis nets are down.

20:45.792 --> 20:47.760
[chuckles]

20:56.503 --> 20:58.370
Datak. Stahma.

20:58.405 --> 21:02.942
Exciting news from my spies
outside of Defiance.

21:02.976 --> 21:06.345
The gulanite shortage
has apparently forced the town

21:06.379 --> 21:09.682
to pull the plug
on the stasis nets.

21:09.716 --> 21:11.550
Cause for celebration, no?

21:11.585 --> 21:13.652
You'll overrun them easily.

21:13.687 --> 21:15.120
And that pleases you?

21:15.155 --> 21:17.122
Of course, Favi Tak.

21:18.959 --> 21:21.627
General Rahm Tak.

21:21.661 --> 21:24.163
I know I'm not supposed
to take this job personally,

21:24.197 --> 21:29.301
but I must admit, I'm going
to enjoy this campaign.

21:29.336 --> 21:33.906
I mean, the very idea
of Defiance turns my stomach.

21:33.940 --> 21:35.908
I don't know
how you two lived there.

21:35.942 --> 21:39.044
You know, I think
I will hook a cable to that arch

21:39.079 --> 21:41.380
and pull the whole thing
to the ground.

21:41.414 --> 21:44.617
Perhaps they'll put a statue
of me in its place.

21:44.651 --> 21:47.519
That is a beautiful dream.

21:47.554 --> 21:49.888
Was that sarcasm?

21:49.923 --> 21:54.193
Because I assure you, Favi Tarr,
my aspirations are achievable.

21:54.227 --> 21:56.895
I am not a delusional man.

22:01.067 --> 22:09.074
♪ ♪

22:17.817 --> 22:20.152
There's our signaler.

22:20.186 --> 22:23.489
The one holding
the wormhole flare gun.

22:23.523 --> 22:26.392
I've seen him in Defiance.

22:26.426 --> 22:27.893
They don't look
like soldiers.

22:27.927 --> 22:29.962
Why are they signaling
the V.C.?

22:29.996 --> 22:31.897
That's because they're spies.

22:36.002 --> 22:38.837
Go around to the right.

22:38.872 --> 22:40.839
(Nolan)
That one's yours.

22:40.874 --> 22:43.275
I'll get the one
by the truck.

22:43.310 --> 22:51.317
♪ ♪

23:11.571 --> 23:14.573
[grunting]

23:16.476 --> 23:17.476
Don't move.

23:21.581 --> 23:23.982
I said don't move.

23:24.017 --> 23:26.218
You're from Defiance.

23:26.252 --> 23:28.120
They wrote that book
about you.

23:28.154 --> 23:30.823
What book?

23:31.057 --> 23:32.138
_

23:32.628 --> 23:34.211
_

23:34.260 --> 23:36.762
- Drop the gun!
- _

23:36.796 --> 23:38.748
_

23:39.132 --> 23:40.566
No.

23:40.600 --> 23:44.069
No shooting.
No shooting.

23:44.104 --> 23:46.672
We're friends.

23:46.706 --> 23:48.340
I speak English, see?

23:51.978 --> 23:54.313
Oh, look.

23:54.347 --> 23:56.982
You're trembling.

23:57.016 --> 24:01.487
♪ ♪

24:01.521 --> 24:03.088
Ah!

24:03.123 --> 24:10.996
♪ ♪

24:13.466 --> 24:15.167
[both grunting]

24:15.630 --> 24:17.388
_

24:17.651 --> 24:19.273
_

24:21.875 --> 24:24.743
- [gunshot]
- [groans]

24:26.212 --> 24:27.813
Irisa.

24:27.847 --> 24:28.847
Hey!

24:32.519 --> 24:34.386
[grunts]

24:34.421 --> 24:35.654
Come on.

24:40.827 --> 24:42.094
What happened?

24:42.128 --> 24:44.129
My weapon jammed.

24:47.901 --> 24:52.304
[baby crying]

24:52.338 --> 24:54.072
(Pilar)
Let me.

24:54.107 --> 24:56.308
I've had three children,
you know.

24:56.342 --> 24:58.377
You have to keep one of them
chained to the table,

24:58.411 --> 25:00.813
so she won't run away on you.

25:00.847 --> 25:04.650
Oh, I bet you spent all night
thinking up that one.

25:04.684 --> 25:07.753
Check the traps, funny boy.

25:07.787 --> 25:09.254
Getting cold out there.

25:09.289 --> 25:11.623
I'll go.

25:11.658 --> 25:15.127
I need to stretch my legs.

25:15.161 --> 25:16.495
Come on.
Where would I run to?

25:16.529 --> 25:18.564
We're in the middle
of nowhere.

25:18.598 --> 25:21.433
[sighs]
I know you want to kill me.

25:21.468 --> 25:22.734
Mom!

25:22.769 --> 25:23.735
Excuse me?

25:23.770 --> 25:25.037
(Pilar)
And I don't blame you.

25:25.071 --> 25:27.539
I know how mad
both of you are.

25:27.574 --> 25:29.341
But you don't care?

25:29.375 --> 25:30.542
Oh, don't say that.

25:30.577 --> 25:31.844
I care very much.

25:31.878 --> 25:34.780
And yet here we are.

25:34.814 --> 25:37.916
Your parents
are terrible people.

25:37.951 --> 25:39.218
They threatened me.

25:39.252 --> 25:41.653
They told me they would kill me
if I stayed in Defiance.

25:41.688 --> 25:42.855
Listen, when they tell...

25:42.889 --> 25:44.923
I could not abandon my family
a second time.

25:44.958 --> 25:49.461
Therefore, I had no choice
but to bring you with me.

25:49.496 --> 25:53.765
Surely, you understand that
as a father.

25:53.800 --> 25:55.100
- [baby coos]
- Shh.

25:55.134 --> 25:57.135
- Sure.
- Sweetheart, hush.

25:57.170 --> 25:58.570
(Pilar)
Then it's settled.

25:58.605 --> 26:00.639
We'll both go.
Unchain him.

26:00.673 --> 26:03.642
[soft dramatic music]

26:03.676 --> 26:11.683
♪ ♪

26:14.487 --> 26:15.821
[mouths words]

26:15.855 --> 26:19.958
♪ ♪

26:19.993 --> 26:22.461
Looks like E-Rep
pulled up stakes.

26:22.495 --> 26:25.163
- Good.
- Don't be so sure.

26:25.198 --> 26:27.466
Earth Republic was
the only thing keeping the V.C.

26:27.500 --> 26:29.067
out of North America.

26:29.102 --> 26:37.109
♪ ♪

26:41.514 --> 26:44.316
Come on.
[grunts]

26:44.350 --> 26:46.985
Last time we saw Amanda,
she tried to shoot me.

26:47.020 --> 26:50.022
She considered shooting you.

26:50.056 --> 26:54.693
I remind you she didn't actually
pull the trigger.

26:54.727 --> 26:56.028
But, yeah.

26:56.062 --> 26:57.863
Yeah, you stay in the car.

27:03.403 --> 27:05.337
[door opens]

27:06.873 --> 27:08.640
[door closes]

27:18.084 --> 27:22.988
Sure you can spare
the bullets?

27:23.022 --> 27:25.290
Where's Pottinger?

27:25.325 --> 27:28.594
He's gone.

27:28.628 --> 27:30.195
- I'm back in charge.
- What'd you do?

27:30.229 --> 27:31.530
Stuff the ballot box?

27:31.564 --> 27:33.098
This town's on its last legs.

27:33.132 --> 27:36.468
I've been hanging on
by my fingernails.

27:36.502 --> 27:37.869
Where the hell were you?

27:37.904 --> 27:41.340
Trapped under a mile
of solid rock.

27:41.374 --> 27:44.343
How long have we been gone?

27:44.377 --> 27:46.244
Seven months.

27:48.681 --> 27:50.282
Is Irisa...

27:50.316 --> 27:52.551
Downstairs? Yeah.

27:57.991 --> 28:00.058
(Poole)
Excuse me?

28:01.060 --> 28:02.961
I knew it was you.

28:02.996 --> 28:03.996
Irisa.

28:04.030 --> 28:06.531
Can you sign this?

28:06.566 --> 28:09.101
It's for my boyfriend.

28:12.238 --> 28:14.740
What's it feel like
saving the world?

28:14.774 --> 28:16.308
Bet it feels great, huh?

28:21.314 --> 28:22.481
What happened to your head?

28:22.515 --> 28:23.682
[sighs]

28:23.716 --> 28:26.318
[stammers]

28:26.352 --> 28:28.286
Ah!

28:28.321 --> 28:29.554
Stasis nets are down.

28:29.589 --> 28:31.256
What the hell is going on
with that?

28:31.290 --> 28:32.824
[sighs]

28:32.859 --> 28:35.260
- Can't spare the gulanite.
- Well, you're gonna have to.

28:35.294 --> 28:37.129
You got to get them up,
and you got to get them up now.

28:37.163 --> 28:39.765
- You don't understand.
- No.

28:39.799 --> 28:42.601
You don't understand.

28:42.635 --> 28:44.569
- Votanis Collective.
- Mm-hmm.

28:44.604 --> 28:46.138
They're coming for you.

28:51.844 --> 28:54.246
This book's trash.

28:54.280 --> 28:56.248
I won't sign this.

28:58.651 --> 28:59.985
Take a walk, Poole.

29:00.019 --> 29:01.520
But don't you know
who this is?

29:01.554 --> 29:03.689
- Go home, Deputy.
- No, my shift doesn't end for...

29:03.723 --> 29:05.057
Go home!

29:12.298 --> 29:14.599
I'm the lawkeeper now.

29:14.634 --> 29:17.536
[grunting]

29:23.509 --> 29:25.877
These are all the weapons
that are left in the armory?

29:25.912 --> 29:29.347
There was looting
when the E-Rep bugged out.

29:29.382 --> 29:32.117
All right, I guess it's gonna
have to do for a start.

29:32.151 --> 29:33.618
The real issue is power.

29:33.653 --> 29:35.687
We don't get those stasis nets
back up and running,

29:35.722 --> 29:37.255
this war is over
before it begins.

29:37.290 --> 29:38.857
- Come on.
- Where we going?

29:38.891 --> 29:40.592
To the gulanite mines.

29:40.626 --> 29:43.462
- There's no point.
- Why not?

29:43.496 --> 29:45.931
The mines collapsed
the night you disappeared.

29:45.965 --> 29:47.766
The ground hardened
into I don't know what,

29:47.800 --> 29:49.501
but our drills
can't cut through.

29:49.535 --> 29:51.069
Gulanite's down there,
but we can't access it.

29:51.104 --> 29:53.839
And yet somehow Irisa and I
found our way out

29:53.873 --> 29:55.107
and made it to the surface,

29:55.141 --> 29:57.943
so there's got to be a tunnel
or something.

30:00.113 --> 30:02.581
You don't know
how you made it to the surface?

30:02.615 --> 30:04.216
No, but the purple-skins do.

30:04.250 --> 30:05.584
Purple-skins?

30:05.618 --> 30:07.419
I'll tell you on the way.

30:07.453 --> 30:10.455
- [screaming]
- [grunting]

30:11.657 --> 30:13.225
Hey!

30:13.259 --> 30:15.994
Berlin!

30:16.028 --> 30:17.262
Berlin, what the hell
are you doing?

30:17.296 --> 30:21.166
- She killed Tommy!
- A machine killed Tommy!

30:21.200 --> 30:24.503
You lay a hand on her again,
and I don't care who you are,

30:24.537 --> 30:26.838
I will put you in the ground.

30:38.050 --> 30:46.057
♪ ♪

30:52.732 --> 30:54.599
That hardware
always been there?

30:54.634 --> 30:56.067
No. It's new.

30:56.102 --> 30:58.970
Thought you said
no one was home at the mines.

30:59.005 --> 31:00.972
I did.

31:01.007 --> 31:09.014
♪ ♪

31:16.555 --> 31:18.957
Looks like someone
set up shop for themselves.

31:21.661 --> 31:25.196
(Nolan) This tech's Votan.
Indogene.

31:29.535 --> 31:30.835
Looks like
our squatters are

31:30.870 --> 31:32.337
from your neck of the woods,
kiddo.

31:32.371 --> 31:34.439
I'm from Denver.

31:37.643 --> 31:40.345
Oh, baby.

31:40.379 --> 31:42.213
Come to papa.

31:42.248 --> 31:45.116
Purples took my gun, so we know
we're in the right place.

31:47.386 --> 31:49.321
They have terraformers.

31:53.547 --> 31:54.792
What the hell was that?

31:59.815 --> 32:00.782
I'm not waiting to find out.

32:00.816 --> 32:03.585
[gunshots]

32:03.619 --> 32:05.687
Ah!

32:05.721 --> 32:06.988
[gunshots]

32:07.022 --> 32:08.957
[drone shrieks]

32:15.965 --> 32:17.131
Strong pulse.

32:17.166 --> 32:19.500
She's just stunned.
Come on.

32:19.535 --> 32:23.271
♪ ♪

32:23.305 --> 32:25.707
(Nolan) On me.
You cover right.

32:25.741 --> 32:29.477
[indistinct chatter]

32:29.511 --> 32:32.814
Rahm Tak...
[speaks native language]

32:32.848 --> 32:35.350
[indistinct chatter continues]

32:35.384 --> 32:37.318
- Is there something wrong?
- No talking.

32:39.955 --> 32:41.356
Come.

32:41.390 --> 32:42.724
Quickly.

32:42.758 --> 32:45.727
[vehicle engine starts]

32:45.761 --> 32:54.736
♪ ♪

32:54.770 --> 32:56.337
We found some humans.

32:56.372 --> 32:57.605
Should be educational.

32:57.640 --> 33:05.647
♪ ♪

33:10.352 --> 33:13.521
Well, somebody's been busy
down here.

33:13.555 --> 33:16.524
[mysterious music]

33:16.558 --> 33:25.166
♪ ♪

33:25.200 --> 33:28.136
What the hell do they want
with all this gulanite?

33:28.170 --> 33:36.177
♪ ♪

33:54.797 --> 33:56.964
[snarls]

34:13.681 --> 34:16.117
I want to get my hands
on one of those drones.

34:16.150 --> 34:17.585
Figure out how they work,

34:17.619 --> 34:22.056
we might get a bead on who
or what we're dealing with here.

34:22.091 --> 34:24.092
[snarls]

34:24.126 --> 34:27.728
Whoa.

34:27.763 --> 34:29.597
I remember you.

34:29.630 --> 34:30.998
[snarls]

34:31.033 --> 34:33.568
You want to tell us
what you're doing in our mines?

34:33.601 --> 34:34.902
[all grunting]

34:34.937 --> 34:37.905
[tense music]

34:37.940 --> 34:45.947
♪ ♪

34:55.357 --> 34:57.291
Oh, feeling frisky, are we?

35:00.095 --> 35:01.863
[snarls]

35:05.634 --> 35:07.402
Drop the weapon!

35:07.436 --> 35:09.670
Drop it!

35:09.705 --> 35:10.838
[gunshots]

35:14.777 --> 35:16.110
You guys okay?

35:16.145 --> 35:17.545
Yeah.

35:17.579 --> 35:19.046
Did you have to shoot her
in the gut?

35:19.081 --> 35:21.382
- I was aiming for the legs.
- Nice aim.

35:21.417 --> 35:23.851
Look, I'm a little shaky after
being zapped by that thing.

35:23.886 --> 35:25.753
Is she gonna live?

35:25.788 --> 35:27.688
Not unless we get her
to a doctor fast.

35:27.723 --> 35:29.223
Grab the roller.

35:31.927 --> 35:39.434
♪ ♪

35:39.468 --> 35:42.403
[baby crying]

35:48.310 --> 35:50.111
It's V.C. patrol.

35:50.145 --> 35:51.446
I'm gonna go talk to them.

35:51.480 --> 35:52.814
Then unlock the chain first.

35:52.848 --> 35:54.449
Mom wouldn't like that.

35:54.483 --> 35:56.284
Luke is half Casti,
half human.

35:56.318 --> 35:57.552
Do you know
what the Votanis Collective

35:57.586 --> 35:59.420
does to mixed-breed babies?

36:08.430 --> 36:10.131
Find a good hiding place.

36:16.271 --> 36:19.273
[indistinct chatter]

36:24.205 --> 36:25.395
_

36:26.200 --> 36:29.080
_

36:29.117 --> 36:30.885
Yeah, yeah.
Boring, boring.

36:35.891 --> 36:37.658
Do you know who I am?

36:37.693 --> 36:38.793
Rahm Tak.

36:40.186 --> 36:41.471
_

36:42.264 --> 36:44.499
I'm on your side.

36:44.533 --> 36:47.034
I worked as a spy
for the Collective.

36:47.069 --> 36:50.304
I assassinated Earth Republic
Ambassador Tennety.

36:50.339 --> 36:52.340
What did you say
your name was?

36:52.374 --> 36:55.076
Quentin McCawley.

36:55.110 --> 36:57.211
McCawley.

36:57.246 --> 37:01.716
McCawley, McCawley, McCawley,
McCawley, McCawley, McCawley.

37:04.319 --> 37:05.553
Never heard of you.

37:05.587 --> 37:06.587
[gunshot]

37:07.923 --> 37:11.292
Ah! No!

37:11.326 --> 37:14.228
[Rafe screams]

37:14.263 --> 37:19.800
♪ ♪

37:19.835 --> 37:23.871
[screams]

37:23.906 --> 37:26.007
Oops.

37:26.041 --> 37:28.042
Was that your son?

37:28.076 --> 37:30.511
- No!
- McCawl...

37:30.546 --> 37:35.283
♪ ♪

37:38.755 --> 37:41.518
There was
no reason to kill him.

37:41.538 --> 37:45.241
He just did it out of spite.

37:45.275 --> 37:47.944
I'm sorry, Rafe.

37:47.978 --> 37:51.714
As family,
we will bear this <i>zoruto</i>

37:51.749 --> 37:55.551
and take vengeance together.

37:55.586 --> 37:57.720
Thanks, Datak.
It means a lot.

37:57.755 --> 37:59.889
(Stahma)
Someone's coming.

38:03.594 --> 38:05.294
The general's
asking for you two.

38:36.426 --> 38:41.531
Stahma, you said you captured
"Papa Bear" McCawley

38:41.565 --> 38:43.065
somewhere around here, right?

38:43.100 --> 38:44.333
Yes.

38:44.368 --> 38:47.270
And yet you failed to notice
that he had a son

38:47.304 --> 38:49.305
running around loose?

38:49.339 --> 38:51.240
We're as surprised
as you must be.

38:51.275 --> 38:52.708
Clever humans.

38:52.743 --> 38:55.278
I'm beginning to think
you're the clever one, Stahma.

38:57.481 --> 39:00.449
[suspenseful music]

39:00.484 --> 39:03.252
♪ ♪

39:03.287 --> 39:05.521
[groaning]

39:05.556 --> 39:13.563
♪ ♪

39:23.774 --> 39:25.174
[loud clatter]

39:25.209 --> 39:33.216
♪ ♪

39:48.332 --> 39:49.332
Ah!

39:53.737 --> 39:54.770
(Bebe)
Look at this.

39:54.805 --> 39:58.174
I found a mouse.

39:58.208 --> 40:01.310
This is a private home.
You have no right to be here!

40:01.345 --> 40:02.378
So?

40:02.412 --> 40:04.513
[gunfire]

40:06.617 --> 40:07.717
The baby.

40:07.751 --> 40:09.018
We need to get the soldiers
out of here.

40:09.052 --> 40:11.587
[gunfire]

40:14.391 --> 40:17.426
[screaming]

40:17.461 --> 40:20.363
[gunfire]

40:22.032 --> 40:24.901
[heartbeat thumping]

40:33.410 --> 40:36.746
[gasps]
No!

40:36.780 --> 40:38.915
Oh, Dad!
[sobbing]

40:42.287 --> 40:44.187
_

40:45.160 --> 40:47.108
_

40:48.290 --> 40:50.143
_

40:50.961 --> 40:52.228
She's... she's in shock.

40:52.262 --> 40:53.262
I am not in shock!

40:53.297 --> 40:57.099
I know exactly what I'm saying!

40:57.134 --> 40:59.568
May your liro stink
of unclean death

40:59.603 --> 41:02.638
in the forever-after
of the Three Hells!

41:02.673 --> 41:04.740
Oh, forgive her.
Please!

41:04.775 --> 41:09.645
Stahma, did you teach this human
the curses of our people?

41:12.649 --> 41:15.885
This is
your husband's charge blade.

41:15.919 --> 41:17.787
I want you to kill this human
with it.

41:17.821 --> 41:19.188
[sobbing]

41:19.222 --> 41:21.190
Do it for me.

41:23.794 --> 41:27.430
I sense hesitation.

41:27.464 --> 41:29.632
Would you kill this human
in exchange

41:29.666 --> 41:31.667
for your husband's life?

41:34.271 --> 41:37.239
Stahma, make a decision.

41:40.010 --> 41:44.580
♪ ♪

41:44.614 --> 41:46.015
- Stahma!
- [whispers] Come.

41:46.049 --> 41:47.750
(Rahm)
Make a decision!

41:47.784 --> 41:55.658
♪ ♪

42:14.244 --> 42:15.745
I'm not afraid.

42:19.483 --> 42:21.350
Aah!

42:21.385 --> 42:23.819
- [gasps]
- No! Oh!

42:23.854 --> 42:24.854
Shh!

42:38.035 --> 42:40.536
Thank you, General,

42:40.570 --> 42:43.539
for providing clarity.

42:43.573 --> 42:48.444
Of course, the only good human
is a dead one.

42:48.478 --> 42:54.383
Favi Tak,
may we leave this place now?

42:54.418 --> 42:57.820
The human death-stink offends.

42:57.854 --> 42:58.821
[Rahm laughs]

42:58.855 --> 43:01.824
Of course.
Move out!

43:20.944 --> 43:23.946
[baby crying]

43:29.894 --> 43:37.918
♪ ♪

43:44.092 --> 43:46.660
[sobbing]
Oh, <i>gao.</i>

43:46.694 --> 43:49.596
Oh, <i>gao.</i>

43:49.631 --> 43:53.467
Oh, Rayetso, <i>gao.</i>

43:53.801 --> 43:55.136
_

43:56.135 --> 43:58.585
_

43:58.740 --> 44:02.676
[screams]

44:02.710 --> 44:04.878
[wails]

44:04.913 --> 44:07.881
[baby crying]

44:07.916 --> 44:14.021
♪ ♪

44:14.055 --> 44:17.257
Luke? Luke?

44:17.292 --> 44:20.327
He's hungry.

44:20.361 --> 44:24.231
Oh, baby, thank God.

44:24.265 --> 44:29.803
You remember how our kids
used to cry like that...

44:29.837 --> 44:33.206
when they were...

44:34.309 --> 44:36.643
Oh, Rafe.

44:36.678 --> 44:40.080
Rafe McCawley,
you wake the hell up right now.

44:40.114 --> 44:43.350
[breathing heavily]

44:43.384 --> 44:46.386
[baby coos]

44:55.196 --> 44:58.598
[Rafe chuckles]

44:58.633 --> 45:00.567
Oh...

45:03.972 --> 45:08.809
Alak, my son, you forget
what happened here.

45:08.843 --> 45:11.812
You forget this day,

45:11.846 --> 45:16.216
and you love this little baby
like you loved my Christie.

45:16.250 --> 45:18.552
I should have been better.

45:18.586 --> 45:23.490
Well, me too.

45:23.524 --> 45:29.229
♪ ♪

45:29.263 --> 45:32.699
[baby crying]

45:32.734 --> 45:36.703
[Alak crying]

45:36.738 --> 45:44.244
♪ ♪

45:44.278 --> 45:45.645
What are you doing?

45:45.680 --> 45:48.515
Waste not, want not.

46:03.131 --> 46:04.664
What's with all
the cloak and dagger?

46:04.699 --> 46:05.932
We're keeping this quiet.

46:05.967 --> 46:07.000
We don't want anyone
to see her.

46:07.035 --> 46:09.136
Why? Who's the patient?

46:12.907 --> 46:16.043
[ominous music]

46:16.377 --> 46:17.878
_

46:18.613 --> 46:19.613
Can you help her?

46:19.647 --> 46:21.314
I'm not going anywhere
near that thing!

46:21.349 --> 46:22.749
Let nature take its course!

46:22.784 --> 46:23.917
If you stand by
and let her die,

46:23.951 --> 46:25.585
we're gonna
be digging two graves.

46:32.860 --> 46:35.695
Fine, chain her up.

46:35.730 --> 46:37.164
Doc, she's half dead.

46:37.198 --> 46:38.965
An optimist would say
she's half alive.

46:39.000 --> 46:40.534
Chain her up.

46:44.308 --> 46:46.943
Come on.

46:46.978 --> 46:48.812
So you know what she is?

46:48.846 --> 46:50.947
She's a predator
designed by evolution

46:50.982 --> 46:52.215
to conquer, kill,
and devour.

46:52.250 --> 46:53.583
She moves like a hunter.

46:53.618 --> 46:55.252
Yeah, well,
she eats like a cannibal.

46:55.286 --> 46:57.420
What kind of Votan is she?

46:57.455 --> 47:00.156
There was
an early Votan race,

47:00.191 --> 47:01.925
one that predated
the rest of us,

47:01.959 --> 47:04.961
one that called the shots
for a very long time.

47:07.798 --> 47:09.232
Congratulations,

47:09.267 --> 47:11.902
you found yourselves
an honest-to-goodness Omec.

47:11.936 --> 47:15.272
Omec? I've heard the name,
but I heard they died out.

47:15.306 --> 47:16.773
(Yewll)
Supposedly they did.

47:16.807 --> 47:20.644
Back home we built arcs
to escape the exploding sun.

47:20.678 --> 47:23.780
Ours worked.
Theirs didn't.

47:23.814 --> 47:27.717
[speaking native language]

47:30.588 --> 47:32.422
Hey, we don't
mean you any harm.

47:40.498 --> 47:42.365
Conquer, kill, devour.

47:42.400 --> 47:45.402
Put it on a T-shirt,
so you don't forget.

47:45.436 --> 47:47.637
(Amanda) According to Nolan,
there's another one.

47:47.672 --> 47:51.308
- A male.
- Kill them both.

47:51.342 --> 47:55.011
You have no idea
what you're dealing with.

47:55.046 --> 47:58.014
[dramatic music]

47:58.049 --> 48:01.418
♪ ♪

48:14.865 --> 48:16.766
That should keep you warm.

48:24.675 --> 48:27.243
[groans]

48:27.578 --> 48:29.286
_

48:31.420 --> 48:34.328
_

48:34.905 --> 48:35.706
_

48:37.088 --> 48:39.556
Good right hook.
[laughs]

48:39.590 --> 48:41.691
Ka-pow.

48:41.726 --> 48:44.027
Ka-pow.

48:57.241 --> 48:58.842
Warm.

48:58.876 --> 49:01.044
[growls]

49:06.384 --> 49:09.052
That's it.

49:09.086 --> 49:10.820
Nice and warm.

49:15.426 --> 49:16.826
Very flattering.

49:25.770 --> 49:28.838
<i>T'abinel</i> Kindzi.

49:28.873 --> 49:30.874
Nolan.

49:32.910 --> 49:34.911
Irisa.

49:37.014 --> 49:39.716
[sniffs]

49:39.750 --> 49:43.520
What the doc said
about you guys being cannibals,

49:43.554 --> 49:45.221
back there in the caves

49:45.256 --> 49:47.157
when you licked me...

49:47.191 --> 49:50.060
[groans]

49:53.931 --> 49:55.632
You weren't gonna eat me,
were you?

49:55.666 --> 49:56.966
[snarls]

49:57.001 --> 50:00.070
[laughs]

50:00.104 --> 50:01.871
You understand me,
don't you?

50:06.343 --> 50:11.981
♪ ♪

50:12.016 --> 50:13.550
[sighs]

50:15.686 --> 50:17.554
Oh, um,

50:17.588 --> 50:20.156
what brings you to my stall
this fine afternoon?

50:20.191 --> 50:22.459
Favi Ksaruko, hello.

50:22.493 --> 50:25.495
Monguno, how's it going
with that mandolin of yours?

50:25.529 --> 50:29.065
- Fine.
- He doesn't practice enough.

50:29.100 --> 50:31.701
Uh, how can I help you,
Madam Mayor?

50:31.736 --> 50:34.871
Yes, um,
a Votan friend of mine

50:34.905 --> 50:38.341
was telling me a story today
about the Omec.

50:38.375 --> 50:41.678
Um, "devils,"

50:41.712 --> 50:43.146
as you humans would say.

50:43.180 --> 50:45.415
Enchanters.

50:45.449 --> 50:47.851
Takers of the innocent.

50:47.885 --> 50:49.853
Dark gods.

50:49.887 --> 50:51.554
(Amanda)
Would you call them cannibals?

50:51.589 --> 50:53.356
Only if I were
a sloppy speaker.

50:53.390 --> 50:54.991
Cannibals

50:55.025 --> 50:59.062
eat their own species
whereas Omec,

50:59.096 --> 51:02.165
they preferred eating us.

51:04.018 --> 51:07.593
_

51:07.964 --> 51:10.766
_

51:10.851 --> 51:17.926
_

51:18.849 --> 51:21.017
<i>Thudu thezuhu,</i>

51:21.051 --> 51:24.621
"The Dread Harvest."

51:24.655 --> 51:28.424
Every 76 years,
the Omec home planet,

51:28.459 --> 51:30.593
which is here,

51:30.628 --> 51:34.297
would come close
to the other Votan planets.

51:34.331 --> 51:37.367
The Omec came
in giant space vessels

51:37.401 --> 51:40.436
and spirited away
thousands upon thousands

51:40.471 --> 51:42.438
of our ancestors.

51:42.473 --> 51:46.309
Those harvested were kept
as slaves

51:46.343 --> 51:49.412
until their Omec masters
grew bored.

51:49.446 --> 51:51.748
- Or hungry?
- Exactly.

51:53.350 --> 51:55.685
Those old stories are bogus.

51:55.719 --> 51:58.721
Bogus?

51:58.756 --> 52:01.457
You ignore your people's history
at your own peril.

52:01.492 --> 52:04.460
I don't believe in Omec.

52:04.495 --> 52:08.398
That's because you are
a foolish boy with work to do.

52:08.432 --> 52:10.433
Go.

52:12.236 --> 52:14.637
Pay no attention to my son.

52:14.672 --> 52:17.740
The Omec were very real,

52:17.775 --> 52:19.776
very dangerous.

52:19.810 --> 52:21.077
[door slams]

52:21.111 --> 52:24.080
[overlapping shouting]

52:24.114 --> 52:27.083
[suspenseful music]

52:27.117 --> 52:29.752
♪ ♪

52:29.787 --> 52:31.588
[growls softly]

52:31.622 --> 52:34.791
♪ ♪

52:34.825 --> 52:37.861
I'm here for my daughter.

52:41.000 --> 52:43.467
[indistinct conversations]

52:43.545 --> 52:44.912
All well and good, General,

52:44.947 --> 52:49.150
but Defiance will not
go down without a fight.

52:49.184 --> 52:51.319
How do you plan
to take the city

52:51.353 --> 52:53.988
with such a small force?

52:54.022 --> 52:55.456
We have a weapon.

52:55.490 --> 52:57.091
What kind of weapon?

52:57.125 --> 52:59.994
She said it's our little secret,
and by golly, oh,

53:00.028 --> 53:02.563
I'm gonna keep it.

53:02.598 --> 53:04.265
It's from a Johnny Cash song.

53:04.299 --> 53:06.601
Ah, the <i>Man in Black.</i>

53:06.635 --> 53:08.236
For a southern member
of the Collective,

53:08.270 --> 53:11.739
your command of human culture,
General, is... is excellent.

53:11.773 --> 53:13.841
After emigrating,
I studied in New York.

53:13.875 --> 53:17.678
I lived with them.
I ate with them.

53:17.713 --> 53:19.547
I know everything
there is to know

53:19.581 --> 53:21.182
about everything human.

53:21.216 --> 53:24.452
Living with pigs, one grows
all too accustomed to filth.

53:24.486 --> 53:26.554
Praise Rayetso.

53:26.588 --> 53:29.156
But please
don't misunderstand,

53:29.191 --> 53:32.693
I desire that filth.

53:32.728 --> 53:35.830
Consider sweet
Lieutenant Bebe,

53:35.864 --> 53:38.532
an Indogene
who wore a human skin

53:38.567 --> 53:41.869
to infiltrate a shopping mall,
killing hundreds of humans.

53:41.903 --> 53:43.337
His skin is heroic.

53:43.372 --> 53:44.805
I call it poetry.

53:44.840 --> 53:47.375
We shall seize
their human language,

53:47.409 --> 53:50.711
their land, their clothes,

53:50.746 --> 53:53.147
the very skin on their faces.

53:53.181 --> 53:56.250
Everything in this world
is ours for the taking.

53:59.054 --> 54:02.556
"Manifest Destiny."

54:02.591 --> 54:04.191
Do you know the term?

54:04.226 --> 54:06.560
Oh, I know
it's a human concept.

54:06.595 --> 54:09.630
So well informed...

54:09.665 --> 54:12.166
both of you.

54:12.200 --> 54:15.536
- You honor us, General.
- _

54:15.570 --> 54:18.005
I shame myself.

54:20.976 --> 54:24.378
So I am trying to decide

54:24.413 --> 54:27.014
how best to put
you both to work

54:27.049 --> 54:29.183
for the Votan cause.

54:29.217 --> 54:32.520
Anything to serve
the Collective, General.

54:32.554 --> 54:34.522
Good, good,
because you, Datak,

54:34.556 --> 54:37.992
are going to be a saboteur
for the Votanis Collective.

54:38.026 --> 54:41.095
You are gonna help me
bring that odious little town

54:41.129 --> 54:44.231
to its knees.

54:44.266 --> 54:48.736
If I may, General...

54:48.770 --> 54:51.472
without me there
to calm him,

54:51.506 --> 54:56.711
my husband is prone
to fits of intemperate anger.

54:56.745 --> 54:59.180
You're saying
I should send you both?

54:59.214 --> 55:02.783
It might help you achieve
the objective you desire.

55:04.519 --> 55:07.088
Here's the thing, Stahma,

55:07.122 --> 55:10.991
you and your husband are
a pair of treacherous snakes.

55:11.026 --> 55:13.527
If I release you both, you'll
disappear into the woodpile,

55:13.562 --> 55:15.229
and I won't get what I want.

55:15.263 --> 55:17.031
So I think it's best
for everyone

55:17.065 --> 55:19.934
if we set
some simple ground rules.

55:19.968 --> 55:21.936
You, Datak,
will go to Defiance.

55:21.970 --> 55:25.272
You'll carry out assignments
that I give you.

55:25.307 --> 55:29.243
Anytime you refuse
an assignment or fail

55:29.277 --> 55:32.813
or displease me
in any way,

55:32.848 --> 55:35.983
I will cut a piece off
of your wife's beautiful body.

55:36.017 --> 55:38.586
And over time,

55:38.620 --> 55:42.156
that can add up
to one ugly bitch.

55:42.190 --> 55:45.359
So do as I say.

55:52.134 --> 55:54.435
Do you even know
where we're going?

55:54.469 --> 55:56.971
As long as the Collective
are far behind us,

55:57.005 --> 55:59.039
I could care less.

56:00.675 --> 56:02.410
Oh, I know.

56:02.444 --> 56:04.745
I know, baby.

56:04.780 --> 56:08.115
I'm so sorry
your terrible Casti grandparents

56:08.150 --> 56:10.351
ruined everything.

56:10.385 --> 56:12.386
I will protect you.

56:21.496 --> 56:24.865
What are you gonna do?

56:24.900 --> 56:28.102
I am going to get food
for my grandson.

56:37.469 --> 56:39.437
She'll be back.

56:39.471 --> 56:41.372
It's gonna be okay.

56:48.514 --> 56:50.548
[knocks at door]

56:51.784 --> 56:53.785
Please...

56:53.819 --> 56:56.821
[speaking indistinctly]

57:09.234 --> 57:11.836
Help her up.

57:17.776 --> 57:18.843
[gunshots]

57:18.877 --> 57:22.647
[gasps]

57:26.819 --> 57:28.853
I found these in our mines

57:28.887 --> 57:31.222
along with my daughter's blood.

57:33.258 --> 57:36.761
Well, you have nothing
to worry about.

57:36.795 --> 57:38.696
She's fine.

57:38.731 --> 57:39.964
Where is she?

57:39.998 --> 57:42.100
Why don't you answer
some questions first?

57:42.134 --> 57:44.368
Take me to her.

57:48.407 --> 57:49.841
Listen,
I appreciate your patience

57:49.875 --> 57:51.175
during this trying time,

57:51.210 --> 57:55.179
but forgive me,
I don't know what to call you.

57:55.214 --> 57:59.217
Eksua Tsuroz T'evgin.

57:59.251 --> 58:01.385
Eksua is my family,

58:01.420 --> 58:04.155
Tsuroz is my ship,

58:04.189 --> 58:08.326
and you may call me
T'evgin.

58:08.360 --> 58:11.129
You say you have a ship?

58:11.163 --> 58:12.830
I believe I just did.

58:12.865 --> 58:14.532
Is it functional?

58:14.566 --> 58:18.136
[ominous music]

58:18.170 --> 58:21.105
You are asking
very invasive questions

58:21.140 --> 58:23.641
of someone who just recently
saved your life.

58:23.675 --> 58:26.644
See, I don't know
that you just saved my life.

58:26.678 --> 58:29.213
Mm, I know I woke up
with a gash in my head.

58:29.248 --> 58:32.984
The head wound
was from where the sleeper pod

58:33.018 --> 58:35.686
was hooked into your brain.

58:35.721 --> 58:38.356
The entire system
was losing power,

58:38.390 --> 58:42.693
and you both soon would have
died had I not taken action.

58:42.728 --> 58:46.564
Cutting the interface
was to release you from the pod.

58:46.598 --> 58:49.734
And then you dumped us out
in the snow and left us to die.

58:49.768 --> 58:51.903
You attacked us.

58:51.937 --> 58:53.371
I wanted to kill you,

58:53.405 --> 58:57.041
but my daughter pled mercy
on your behalf.

58:57.075 --> 59:00.478
Speaking of which,
you will take me to her now.

59:00.512 --> 59:02.480
Well, we still
have some more questions

59:02.514 --> 59:04.215
you have to answer.

59:04.249 --> 59:05.783
(Nolan) Like what's
with all the gulanite?

59:05.818 --> 59:08.953
That ship of yours low on power?
Need fuel?

59:08.987 --> 59:12.790
When we arrived in Earth orbit,
our ship was low on fuel

59:12.825 --> 59:14.592
and badly in need of repair.

59:14.626 --> 59:17.395
And what happens once
that ship is functional again?

59:17.429 --> 59:21.265
Others may have survived
like my daughter and I did.

59:21.300 --> 59:23.935
We will travel into deep space
in search for them.

59:23.969 --> 59:27.338
- Just the two of you?
- Yes.

59:30.375 --> 59:32.176
All right,
here's the deal.

59:32.211 --> 59:34.745
Our town needs gulanite badly.

59:34.780 --> 59:38.816
I suggest a sharing agreement,
50/50.

59:38.851 --> 59:41.686
Our mines, your equipment.

59:41.720 --> 59:45.423
Everybody wins.

59:45.457 --> 59:47.758
These are my terms!

59:47.793 --> 59:49.894
You will bring me
my daughter,

59:49.928 --> 59:53.164
or I will bathe in the blood
of every Votan and human

59:53.198 --> 59:55.199
until my rage is cleansed.

59:55.234 --> 59:57.034
Now, where is she?

59:57.069 --> 59:59.036
You finished?

01:00:06.111 --> 01:00:07.745
I shot your daughter.

01:00:07.779 --> 01:00:11.082
But she attacked me first, which
means I was within my rights.

01:00:11.116 --> 01:00:13.885
We brought her back to town
to seek medical care.

01:00:13.919 --> 01:00:16.454
She's stable,
and she's resting comfortably.

01:00:16.488 --> 01:00:18.556
Now, I will return her to you

01:00:18.590 --> 01:00:22.360
when you and I reach
an agreement about the gulanite.

01:00:22.394 --> 01:00:26.097
So she's a hostage?

01:00:26.131 --> 01:00:28.466
No, that's an ugly word.

01:00:35.440 --> 01:00:38.276
[screams]

01:00:41.713 --> 01:00:43.214
- Should be you.
- What?

01:00:43.248 --> 01:00:44.482
Chained up.

01:00:44.516 --> 01:00:45.716
You're the real menace.

01:00:45.751 --> 01:00:47.752
[door opens]

01:00:49.421 --> 01:00:50.454
Can we see it?

01:00:50.489 --> 01:00:52.189
There's nothing
to see, short stuff.

01:00:52.224 --> 01:00:55.259
Mayor came to my dad's booth
asking about Omec,

01:00:55.294 --> 01:00:57.762
and then one showed up
outside the NeedWant.

01:00:57.796 --> 01:00:59.397
What? You see Omec?

01:00:59.431 --> 01:01:01.399
Didn't your dad beat you once
for calling him "Omec"?

01:01:01.433 --> 01:01:02.533
There's nothing in here.

01:01:02.567 --> 01:01:04.035
Then why is she
guarding the door?

01:01:04.069 --> 01:01:06.604
Leave, now.

01:01:06.638 --> 01:01:08.439
Don't piss her off.

01:01:08.473 --> 01:01:10.241
She'll drop an ark
on your head.

01:01:13.145 --> 01:01:15.713
You are her, from book.

01:01:15.747 --> 01:01:18.282
Goddess of Badland.

01:01:18.317 --> 01:01:20.017
That book's trash.

01:01:20.052 --> 01:01:22.486
<i>Shtako,</i> that is her.

01:01:22.521 --> 01:01:23.487
Why didn't you kill it?

01:01:23.522 --> 01:01:25.256
That Omec?
You kill everything.

01:01:25.290 --> 01:01:27.425
You are murder.

01:01:27.459 --> 01:01:31.128
Okay, boys, that's enough.
Bye.

01:01:31.163 --> 01:01:34.165
[boys laughing and chattering]

01:01:39.304 --> 01:01:41.105
You are murder.

01:01:45.577 --> 01:01:47.311
She bitch.

01:01:47.346 --> 01:01:49.847
[clangs]

01:01:49.881 --> 01:01:51.148
Guys, she lied.

01:01:51.183 --> 01:01:52.750
There's totally an Omec in here.

01:01:52.784 --> 01:01:55.553
Check it out.

01:01:55.587 --> 01:01:57.221
- Hey, yo, boost me up.
- All right.

01:01:57.255 --> 01:02:00.358
[Kindzi snarls]

01:02:00.392 --> 01:02:03.327
- What do you see?
- I don't know, it's dark.

01:02:03.362 --> 01:02:07.064
[boys pounding on wall]

01:02:07.099 --> 01:02:10.601
Here, Omec.
Come here, little Omec.

01:02:10.635 --> 01:02:11.969
(Wannabe)
Poke it.

01:02:12.004 --> 01:02:13.104
[loud thud and screaming]

01:02:13.138 --> 01:02:14.872
[gasps]

01:02:14.906 --> 01:02:17.508
- [loud clanging]
- She's still chained up, right?

01:02:17.542 --> 01:02:19.210
What did you see?
What did you see?

01:02:23.648 --> 01:02:25.683
(Monguno)
Come here, girlie.

01:02:25.717 --> 01:02:27.985
Come on. Come on.

01:02:28.020 --> 01:02:29.020
[gasps]

01:02:29.054 --> 01:02:32.023
(Wannabe)
What happened?

01:02:32.057 --> 01:02:33.290
What do you see,
Monguno?

01:02:33.325 --> 01:02:34.525
[Kindzi shouts]

01:02:37.763 --> 01:02:39.597
Get away from there!

01:02:42.100 --> 01:02:43.567
[screams]

01:02:44.703 --> 01:02:46.404
No.

01:02:46.438 --> 01:02:49.073
No, no, no, no, no.

01:02:49.107 --> 01:02:50.074
No.

01:02:50.108 --> 01:02:51.342
- [screaming]
- Please.

01:02:51.376 --> 01:02:53.244
[loud bang]

01:02:53.278 --> 01:02:56.247
[suspenseful music]

01:02:56.281 --> 01:02:58.282
[woman screams in distance]

01:02:58.316 --> 01:03:06.323
♪ ♪

01:03:27.520 --> 01:03:30.908
[indistinct conversations]

01:03:30.924 --> 01:03:33.693
Hey, come on,
out of the way.

01:03:33.727 --> 01:03:36.729
[Yengi speaking native language]

01:03:41.101 --> 01:03:43.202
Omec.

01:03:43.236 --> 01:03:45.805
[speaking native language]

01:03:45.839 --> 01:03:49.075
Is it inconsiderate
to say I told you so?

01:03:49.109 --> 01:03:50.643
I never know
the rules for that.

01:03:50.677 --> 01:03:51.644
[Yengi yelling
in native language]

01:03:51.678 --> 01:03:54.480
Raised by wolves...

01:03:54.514 --> 01:03:55.748
You're not funny.

01:03:55.782 --> 01:03:58.517
50 million Elvis fans
can't be wrong.

01:04:00.695 --> 01:04:02.920
_

01:04:02.990 --> 01:04:04.290
- Get him out of here.
- [people shouting angrily]

01:04:04.324 --> 01:04:06.325
Come on, you trying
to start a riot? Let's go.

01:04:06.360 --> 01:04:07.994
Your Indogene
was insulting.

01:04:08.028 --> 01:04:12.700
_

01:04:12.735 --> 01:04:14.970
_

01:04:22.509 --> 01:04:25.411
[baby crying]

01:04:30.183 --> 01:04:32.451
Well,
at least the baby ate.

01:04:36.256 --> 01:04:38.290
I lost my appetite.

01:04:38.325 --> 01:04:42.261
That little boy
needs his papa to stay strong.

01:04:42.295 --> 01:04:44.663
Family is more important
than anything else

01:04:44.698 --> 01:04:46.632
in this world, Alak.

01:04:46.666 --> 01:04:48.300
You sound like my parents.

01:04:48.335 --> 01:04:50.803
You mean the ones
that killed my daughter?

01:04:50.837 --> 01:04:52.872
Your wife?
His mother?

01:04:52.906 --> 01:04:56.442
No, I very much
do not sound like them.

01:04:56.476 --> 01:04:58.911
You murdered these people.

01:04:58.945 --> 01:05:00.379
How does that make you
any different?

01:05:00.414 --> 01:05:04.917
I kill strangers
to take care of my family.

01:05:04.951 --> 01:05:10.523
Your parents kill family
to take care of themselves.

01:05:21.735 --> 01:05:24.203
[sighs]

01:05:24.237 --> 01:05:29.742
You know, I tried to poison
my three children.

01:05:29.776 --> 01:05:31.877
Christie was just a baby.

01:05:31.912 --> 01:05:35.848
It's come up
in conversation, yeah.

01:05:35.882 --> 01:05:38.918
I was sick.

01:05:38.952 --> 01:05:43.289
The Votan monastery
that Rafe shipped me off to,

01:05:43.323 --> 01:05:45.024
it made me hard,

01:05:45.058 --> 01:05:47.626
but it also taught me

01:05:47.661 --> 01:05:51.597
to look beyond
my own needs.

01:05:51.631 --> 01:05:54.300
I had to suffer

01:05:54.334 --> 01:05:58.270
so that my children
would be safe.

01:05:58.305 --> 01:06:00.306
Safe from you.

01:06:00.340 --> 01:06:02.475
- Right?
- Yes.

01:06:02.509 --> 01:06:07.179
The <i>shigustako</i> offered
redemption,

01:06:07.214 --> 01:06:09.849
Castithan-style.

01:06:09.883 --> 01:06:12.084
I took it.

01:06:12.119 --> 01:06:15.855
I allowed them to abuse me,

01:06:15.889 --> 01:06:19.625
and then my dear,
sweet Quentin found me.

01:06:19.659 --> 01:06:22.862
Forgave me.

01:06:22.896 --> 01:06:25.998
He saved my life...

01:06:26.032 --> 01:06:30.703
because I realized
that my family, my children

01:06:30.737 --> 01:06:33.739
needed a mother.

01:06:33.773 --> 01:06:36.308
I focused on that.

01:06:36.343 --> 01:06:39.945
I wouldn't let anything
stop me,

01:06:39.980 --> 01:06:42.448
least of all your parents.

01:06:44.050 --> 01:06:47.853
[baby cries]

01:06:47.888 --> 01:06:51.557
I am not your mother,
Alak.

01:06:51.591 --> 01:06:55.694
I'm Christie's mother.

01:06:55.729 --> 01:06:59.265
You can depend on me.

01:06:59.299 --> 01:07:01.233
I wish I could believe that.

01:07:01.268 --> 01:07:03.836
I will never betray you.

01:07:15.549 --> 01:07:18.350
Blood trail
comes in from behind us.

01:07:23.857 --> 01:07:25.958
She went this way.

01:07:27.627 --> 01:07:30.196
Must have reopened
her gunshot wounds

01:07:30.230 --> 01:07:32.898
when she escaped.

01:07:32.933 --> 01:07:35.267
I don't like the amount of blood
I'm seeing here.

01:07:37.837 --> 01:07:40.039
How do you think I feel?

01:07:42.375 --> 01:07:43.642
So let's go find her.

01:07:50.317 --> 01:07:51.317
Oh, my God!

01:07:54.487 --> 01:07:56.656
- Do you need a doctor?
- [snarls]

01:07:56.690 --> 01:07:58.391
She needs a doctor!

01:07:58.425 --> 01:07:59.659
(Yengi)
No, she doesn't!

01:07:59.693 --> 01:08:02.695
This Omec killed my son!

01:08:02.729 --> 01:08:04.964
Step away from her,
please.

01:08:04.998 --> 01:08:05.965
[growls]

01:08:05.999 --> 01:08:06.999
_

01:08:07.426 --> 01:08:11.219
_

01:08:11.454 --> 01:08:14.587
_

01:08:15.642 --> 01:08:16.609
Stop!

01:08:16.643 --> 01:08:18.277
Aah!

01:08:19.649 --> 01:08:20.863
_

01:08:21.658 --> 01:08:23.004
_

01:08:25.719 --> 01:08:27.819
[gunshots]

01:08:27.854 --> 01:08:30.656
Get on the ground!
Down!

01:08:30.691 --> 01:08:33.225
All of you, down!
Show me your hands!

01:08:33.260 --> 01:08:35.394
Get that on the ground.

01:08:35.429 --> 01:08:38.898
(Nolan)
Stay down.

01:08:38.932 --> 01:08:40.700
- [growls]
- T'evgin, no!

01:08:40.734 --> 01:08:42.401
No! T'evgin, no!

01:08:42.435 --> 01:08:43.736
Don't worry
about the bookseller.

01:08:43.770 --> 01:08:45.604
Not now.

01:08:45.639 --> 01:08:47.439
Look after your daughter.

01:08:49.109 --> 01:08:51.109
Look at her.

01:09:01.587 --> 01:09:04.590
[screams]

01:09:06.359 --> 01:09:09.060
[indistinct chatter]

01:09:09.095 --> 01:09:12.064
[ominous music]

01:09:12.099 --> 01:09:18.636
♪ ♪

01:09:18.671 --> 01:09:20.005
What is that?

01:09:20.040 --> 01:09:22.374
Call it a letter opener.

01:09:22.408 --> 01:09:23.943
I'll die
before I leave you alone

01:09:23.977 --> 01:09:25.978
here with that <i>decho.</i>

01:09:26.011 --> 01:09:28.380
The McCawleys
may have been human,

01:09:28.415 --> 01:09:30.448
but they were our humans.

01:09:30.484 --> 01:09:33.352
Rafe was shot down
like a dog.

01:09:33.386 --> 01:09:36.055
- He deserved better.
- And Christie?

01:09:42.129 --> 01:09:45.296
Make me a weapon too.

01:09:45.332 --> 01:09:48.768
Better we die together,
don't you think?

01:09:51.904 --> 01:09:53.706
I'll get to work.

01:10:06.019 --> 01:10:07.853
Pilar?

01:10:15.929 --> 01:10:18.898
No, no, no, no, no, no!

01:10:20.700 --> 01:10:22.935
Pilar!

01:10:24.671 --> 01:10:26.505
[grunting]

01:10:32.279 --> 01:10:35.948
Luke!

01:10:35.982 --> 01:10:38.951
[suspenseful music]

01:10:38.985 --> 01:10:46.992
♪ ♪

01:10:48.862 --> 01:10:51.831
[vehicle approaches]

01:10:51.865 --> 01:10:57.570
♪ ♪

01:10:57.604 --> 01:10:59.905
Hey!
Hey, please!

01:10:59.940 --> 01:11:02.308
She... she took my son!

01:11:02.342 --> 01:11:04.176
She took my son!

01:11:04.211 --> 01:11:05.544
She just... she took him!

01:11:05.579 --> 01:11:07.746
[crying]

01:11:07.781 --> 01:11:10.449
Please!
[stammers]

01:11:10.483 --> 01:11:14.420
♪ ♪

01:11:14.454 --> 01:11:16.989
Get the Indogene!
Now!

01:11:17.023 --> 01:11:20.192
Doc, Doc, we got a situation!

01:11:20.227 --> 01:11:21.393
Hey.

01:11:21.428 --> 01:11:23.762
Hey, hey, hey,
sweetheart, hey.

01:11:23.797 --> 01:11:26.131
Look at me.
That's it, focus on me.

01:11:26.166 --> 01:11:27.666
That's it, you stay with me.

01:11:27.701 --> 01:11:29.768
We're gonna get you
through this.

01:11:29.803 --> 01:11:33.472
Hey! Hands off my stuff.

01:11:33.506 --> 01:11:34.607
(Nolan)
Take it easy, Doc.

01:11:34.641 --> 01:11:36.508
Get this monster out of here.

01:11:36.543 --> 01:11:38.811
I'm not gonna ask you twice.

01:11:38.845 --> 01:11:45.517
♪ ♪

01:11:45.552 --> 01:11:47.519
All right,
she's bleeding out.

01:11:47.554 --> 01:11:49.688
She needs your help.

01:11:49.723 --> 01:11:51.457
You misunderstand me.

01:11:51.491 --> 01:11:54.860
I don't need the little
Indogene's medical expertise.

01:11:54.895 --> 01:11:56.862
- I need protoform.
- [screams]

01:11:56.897 --> 01:11:57.997
(Nolan) Whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, whoa.

01:11:58.031 --> 01:12:01.333
Whoa, whoa.
Everybody calm down.

01:12:01.368 --> 01:12:03.135
What exactly is "protoform"?

01:12:03.169 --> 01:12:04.837
Indogene skin.

01:12:04.871 --> 01:12:06.739
The Indogenes are
a manufactured race

01:12:06.773 --> 01:12:08.340
created for many purposes.

01:12:08.375 --> 01:12:10.809
To him, I'm just
a great big tub of spackle.

01:12:10.844 --> 01:12:14.146
- Stay back!
- All right, slow down.

01:12:14.180 --> 01:12:15.881
In order to save
my daughter's life,

01:12:15.916 --> 01:12:17.816
I need a strip of epidermis,

01:12:17.851 --> 01:12:20.853
6 inches long
and 3 inches wide.

01:12:20.887 --> 01:12:24.256
I can promise you that
the Indogene will recover fully.

01:12:24.291 --> 01:12:28.193
Now, out of my way.

01:12:28.228 --> 01:12:33.065
If my daughter dies,
your town dies along with her.

01:12:33.099 --> 01:12:36.235
No gulanite, nothing.

01:12:40.106 --> 01:12:42.641
- Nolan, hold her down.
- What? No!

01:12:42.676 --> 01:12:44.410
- Kiddo.
- I got her.

01:12:44.444 --> 01:12:45.411
Aah!

01:12:45.445 --> 01:12:48.414
♪ ♪

01:12:48.448 --> 01:12:52.217
(Nolan)
All right, come on.

01:12:52.252 --> 01:12:54.086
All right,
I have a sedative.

01:12:54.120 --> 01:12:55.220
(Yewll)
No frigging way!

01:12:55.255 --> 01:12:57.323
Sorry, Doc,
it's necessary.

01:12:57.357 --> 01:12:59.124
Is 20ccs
enough to numb the pain?

01:12:59.159 --> 01:13:00.793
Screw you!

01:13:00.827 --> 01:13:03.890
This is gonna go a lot quicker
if you don't struggle.

01:13:03.925 --> 01:13:08.127
[Yewll screaming]

01:13:08.224 --> 01:13:10.674
[speaking native language]

01:13:14.764 --> 01:13:16.298
[screaming]

01:13:16.333 --> 01:13:19.301
[panting]

01:13:19.336 --> 01:13:22.304
[tense music]

01:13:22.339 --> 01:13:27.976
♪ ♪

01:13:28.011 --> 01:13:30.446
How is she?

01:13:30.480 --> 01:13:33.048
Angry and drugged.

01:13:33.083 --> 01:13:41.090
♪ ♪

01:14:01.544 --> 01:14:04.847
Protoform is
infinitely mutable.

01:14:04.881 --> 01:14:06.548
It has many applications

01:14:06.583 --> 01:14:10.085
that are beneficial
to Omec physiology.

